<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="567" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1015,1040]" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">Discussion.</emphasis>
According to the key for Palaearctic males the species falls to couplet 7 together with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen, 1804)" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[1307,1436,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. femorata</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1804)
</taxonomicName>
, while females to the couplet 9 together with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[838,968,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[838,968,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. femorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1919" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1919" box="[1022,1329,1052,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subinermis">
<emphasis box="[1022,1173,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. subinermis</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1919
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Borkent" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" refString="Borkent, A. &amp; Bissett, B. (1990) A revision of the Holarctic species of Serromyia Meigen (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Systematic Entomology, 15, 153 - 217. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1990. tb 00311. x" type="journal article" year="1990">Borkent &amp; Bissett 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[341,470,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[341,470,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. femorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in presenting totally pale wings, hind coxa without lateral setae, males differ in having fore and mid femora armed with 3 rows of strong bristles and parameres with expanded apices. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subinermis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. subinermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having hind coxa without lateral setae, tibia and femur of fore and mid legs in males armed with numerous strong bristles as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[549,678,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Serromyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femorata">
<emphasis box="[549,678,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="567">S. femorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; parameres slender, with curved apices.
</paragraph>
